cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SY 

The paper deals with reinforcement learning algorithms and their application in visual domains. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since the paper involves the use of a generative model for hallucinating successful trajectories. The paper also involves the use of AI techniques for training reinforcement learning agents, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category. The paper also deals with robotics applications, which makes cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category. Finally, since the paper involves the use of a generative model for training reinforcement learning agents, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category.
